<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-02-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Study of Infectious Agents in Respiratory Diseases</TITLE><BODY>Viruses and bacteria are the main agents that cause respiratory infections in the pediatric population, although, in some circumstances, any pathogenic agent may cause disease. Diagnosis of several pathogens has improved recently. There have been major advances in microbiological diagnosis, particularly in viral detection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>